<p class="">While regretting the fact that the Government have found it necessary to support this resolution regarding the branding of China, and while finding reassurance in the Prime Minister's promise that there will be close association with the United States in an effort to avoid hostilities, may I ask my right hon. Friend whether the Government will continue to use their efforts for an immediate cease-fire, which was the <span id="1087" class="column-number" data-column-number="1087"></span> subject of a special resolution to the United Nations and voted upon? Despite that vote, will the efforts to bring about a cease-fire be persisted in by our Government?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
